```plantuml
@startuml ashavijit_Face-Find
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor black
  Style roundrect
}
left to right direction

actor User

rectangle "Frontend" as FE {
  rectangle "Bootstrap UI" as UI
}

rectangle "Django Backend" as BE {
  rectangle "people/models.py" as Models
  rectangle "people/forms.py" as Forms
  rectangle "people/views.py" as Views
  rectangle "Azure Face API" as AzureAPI #lightyellow
  rectangle "Email Service" as EmailService #lightblue
}

rectangle "Database" as DB #lightgrey

' ========== Connections ==========
User --> UI : Interacts with\nresponsive UI

UI --> FE : Uses Bootstrap CSS\nfor styling

FE --> BE : Sends HTTP requests

BE --> DB : CRUD operations on\nMissingPerson and ReportedPerson

Views --> Models : Interacts with\nmodels for data retrieval

Views --> Forms : Validates data using\nDjango forms

Views --> AzureAPI : Sends requests for\nface ID generation and matching

AzureAPI --> Views : Sends matching results

Views --> EmailService : Sends notifications\nwhen matches found

EmailService --> User : Sends email alerts

' ========== Interactions ==========
User -> UI : Accesses the site
UI -> FE : Loads Bootstrap CSS
FE -> Views : HTTP request to view page
Views -> Models : Query missing persons
Models -> DB : Fetch data
Views -> Forms : Validate data
Forms -> Views : Return validation results
Views -> AzureAPI : Call for face recognition
AzureAPI -> Views : Return recognition results
Views -> EmailService : Send notification email
EmailService -> User : Receive match notification
@enduml
```